Ladysmith Police are investigating a case of murder, after the body of a man was discovered by members of the community, with a stab wound to his neck, along a footpath, in the Acaciaville area, Centenary Road on 3 March. It is alleged that the victim was walking alone in the footpath in the bushes either to or from work, when he was attacked and stabbed to death. There was no cell phone or wallet found in his possession. It is believed that the man could have been robbed and then stabbed by his unknown attackers. Police at this stage are following up on several leads and reviewing forensic evidence. No arrests have been made. Police have requested that if anyone has knowledge about the incident to please come forward and assist in the investigation.